{"fsPath":"/home/khanh/src/0_github/Tardis-1/docs/phase2_tech_evaluation.md","fileUuid":"ac37bdc4-2ec1-40cd-ab59-35e96cba9354","fileSizeBytes":2028,"numLines":70,"diffChanges":[{"originalStartLineNumberOneIndexed":1,"originalEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":1,"modifiedStartLineNumberOneIndexed":1,"modifiedEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":71,"addedLines":["# Phase 2 Technical Evaluation","","## Decision Scope","","Select production-grade technologies for:","","- local-first sync (SQLite to Postgres)","- browser/web execution for adversarial tasks","","## Sync Engine Comparison","","### PowerSync","","Pros:","- Strong offline mutation workflow with client upload queue.","- Local SQLite model aligns with TARDIS Phase 1 architecture.","- Write-path can remain backend-authorized for policy enforcement.","","Cons:","- Additional operational surface area (managed sync service).","- Conflict semantics still need application-level policy.","","### ElectricSQL (electric-next)","","Pros:","- Clean read-sync model from Postgres into clients.","- Good fit for read-heavy experiences.","","Cons:","- Write path not fully handled by sync layer; backend write orchestration remains mandatory.","- Weaker out-of-the-box offline mutation ergonomics than PowerSync.","","### Recommendation","","For TARDIS, prefer **PowerSync-first** once Phase 1 behavior is validated, because misconception/event mutation paths are core and must work offline. Keep ElectricSQL as a fallback for read-dominant UI slices if write semantics are centralized in backend APIs.","","## Execution Plane Comparison","","### WebContainers (JS/Node)","","Pros:","- Excellent browser-native Node/JS execution.","- Fast startup and strong dev UX.","","Cons:","- Not a universal fit for Go/Python execution workloads.","","### Firecracker-Class microVMs (Go/Python)","","Pros:","- Strong isolation and predictable resource controls.","- Language-agnostic execution for backend-like workloads.","","Cons:","- Infrastructure complexity and cold-start management.","","### Recommendation","","Adopt a split execution plane:","","- JS/Node tasks: WebContainers in-browser.","- Go/Python tasks: microVM-backed remote executor API with strict runtime budgets.","","## Migration Gate Criteria","","- Phase 1 retention KPI is stable for 2+ review cycles.","- Misconception precision remains above target.","- Sandbox reliability meets baseline (>=0.98 successful deterministic runs).","- Data model and contracts remain backward-compatible for sync replication.",""],"tokenizedAddedLines":[1000000,1000001,1000002,1000001,1000003,1000001,1000004,1000005,1000001,1000006,1000001,1000007,1000001,1000008,1000009,1000010,1000011,1000001,1000012,1000013,1000014,1000001,1000015,1000001,1000008,1000016,1000017,1000001,1000012,1000018,1000019,1000001,1000020,1000001,1000021,1000001,1000022,1000001,1000023,1000001,1000008,1000024,1000025,1000001,1000012,1000026,1000001,1000027,1000001,1000008,1000028,1000029,1000001,1000012,1000030,1000001,1000020,1000001,1000031,1000001,1000032,1000033,1000001,1000034,1000001,1000035,1000036,1000037,1000038,1000001]}],"gitInfo":{"gitInfo":{"gitRoot":"/home/khanh/src/0_github/Tardis-1","branch":"main","commitHash":"fcbc4c272962a55f6dbf1e27d263242d5a96971f"}},"kind":"KIND_ADDED"}